reviews.review_text: Love this place! Love how easy they make it for me to choose something healthy to eat even when time barely allows it! The grab and go sandwiches are tasty and I can t get enough of their delicious cookies. I also happened to have attended an event recently and was pleasantly surprised to have found Peqish catered it. Their spread looked wonderful. Will for sure keep them in mind if I need catering in the future.

Company with very strong values, welcoming and supportive. Peqish is a good company to work for. As Key Accounts Manager, I am doing a beautiful experience and I have a great work-life balance. I like the values of this company and their mission to assist people in being able to Eat Healthy on the go. Doctors and Chef really take care about peoples health and they are always looking for innovative recipes to create good and tasty products. Our food, low sugar, without preservative and additive tastes amazing. Excellent people to work with, all the staff is very supportive and hard working for the best of our company. The owners are very wise, knowing and supportive. There are many opportunity to learn and grow.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your nice words Laura. It is truly a pleasure to work alongside of you and we are glad that you have joined us on the Key Accounts side.

reviews.review_text: I can t thank Peqish enough for bringing to Vancouver what we so desperately needed.  Their food is delicious, healthy and very reasonably priced.  I have used them for catering as well as just picked up a sandwich or cookie when I am on the go.  I love their brand and LOVE the fact that it was started by PhDs who see intake of food as medicine that can dramatically effect your health. It is time for a change and how great is it that clean and healthy food also tastes so freakishly good??? Keep up the goodness Peqish people.

Finally a great place to buy (actually) healthy, quality food! It s so good!! Their cookies and energy balls are unbelievably yum! It s also really comforting to know that no matter what I buy from Peqish I can trust it s going to be healthy. I m so glad I came across this place. Oh yes, and the service is amazing too! Such a nice bonus :)

Unbelievable catering service. First of all.. very reasonable pricing. The food is outstanding, especially the classic turkey dinner. They re twist on a stuffing is what breaks them apart from the rest. I d have to say their desert is #1 however. Highly recommend!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Joe. Happy to make that stuffin anytime for you. The apple galette with the salted caramel and candied pecan vanilla bean ice cream was a great end to a wonderful meal together. This year, you have to try our flourless chocolate explosion. a healthy, low sugar version of a chocolate lava cake.

reviews.review_text: THE most delicious, healthy dishes. The salad pots are a full of flavour and filling with out giving the heavy feeling after eating. This is my go to lunch spot. I couldnt recommend Peqish more highly if I tried. Developed by Doctors and nutritionists, this brand knows exactly how to feed, fill and nurture.  Big Thumps Up.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Sarah, thanks for the 5-star rating. Glad that you enjoy the food and feel good after you eat it. Our mission is to enable people whom are leading active and busy lifestyles to Eat Healthy on-the Go. A big part of this commitment to producing better-for-you foods centers on the fact that we focus on either making either making the ingredients used in our food or sourcing from like-minded suppliers. Eat in good health!

reviews.review_text: Peqishs vegan/gluten friendly better for you cookie is a must. Its delicious,  low in sugar and satisfies my craving for a bakery item. Love this item and excited for its relaunch!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: We will be relaunching in time for the Holiday Season, and will have a goodie bag just for you!!!

reviews.review_text: Peqish offers the right mix of quality and convenience that is sorely needed in Vancouver. Its the ideal place to grab a healthy on-the-go meal for any student or professional needing high quality ingredient slow food thats fast to get. Especially appealing to anyone craving for a local Pret-a-Manger.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks KZ...Quality together with convenience for healthy better-for-you foods that are meticulously created is something that is so important for us. Pret-A-Manger is an inspiration to us at Peqish.

reviews.review_text: Amazing brand philosophy, super delicious and yet very healthy sandwiches, salads, and wraps. Youre on the right track, Peqish. Hope to see more of your food and message reach a bigger consumer base quickly.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Varun. You can order direct from us for your next event, or through Spud as well as in select locations across the lower mainland.

reviews.review_text: The food is absolutely wonderful, from preparation to presentation, very pleasing. We used Peqish for catering services and they always impress with their many healthy and delicious options.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Simran. Glad that you enjoy our healthy options.

reviews.review_text: This is my go to restaurant. Love the  Eat Right Now philosopy since Ive dietary restrictions and lot of what is on offer suits my palate. We use their catering services as well at least once/twice a month.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Siraj. Always happy to serve you and the rest of your colleagues.

reviews.review_text: Prequish provided catering for our daughter s birthday party. Food was outstanding, and service communication was excellent. Highly Recommend! Would definitely use again for future events
reviews.response_from_owner_text: thanks Nelson, we really enjoyed catering your daughters 1st birthday.

reviews.review_text: love this place!!!  Healthy and tasty breakfast and lunch options.  The best smoothies. They also have excellent choices for catering, lunch & learns and corporate events.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Shawna. Happy to cater more of your lunch & learns.  Hope the last one at St. Pauls went well.

reviews.review_text: Great company, I love the salad and wraps. Everything is made from scratch , If you like healthy style, you have to visit soon!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Barbora. We appreciate the 5-star review and you will definitely be first in-line to receive a goodie basket of our hazelnut hemp bites.

reviews.review_text: Best chocolate chip cookie in town! The ingredient is clean, the texture and taste are absolutely on point!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: the perfect cookie takes care and attention to create. our old fashioned chocolate chunk cookie is a fav. we start off with real butter and whip it with organic  cane sugar and brown sugar. add eggs and vanilla together with sea salt. we then add Canadian flour and finish off with semisweet dark chocolate chunks.

reviews.review_text: Amazing food that is fresh and healthy! I would recommend it to everyone and if you are in the area, definitely check them out :)
Great food, I like their wraps to go. Good simple real recipes

People need to talk about this place more!! The food is great and the service is impeccable! Will definitely come back when I can.

Great service and delicious food!!  The staff is Amazing at catering events !

the cookies are so yummy, also coffee. For this price great.

reviews.review_text: This is a good spot to grab quick food like sandwiches, wraps, cookies, and coffee - on a street thats lacking these kind of options. The service is VERY friendly and most things taste good. My only reservation is that there isnt always good value for money. For example, the sandwiches taste nice but they dont have many toppings for the price.

A great option for office catering or a quick grab-and-go lunch. Catering service and delivery is excellent. Limited seating available inside and items go quick so after-rush is slim pickings. Always fresh and delicious. Portions appear smallish but are more filling than youd think.

One of those rare gems that understands that fast food doesnt have to mean bad food. Fresh, flavourful, and inventive recipes that are ready-to-go when you are... what more can you ask for, all in the heart of busy downtown Vancouver?
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Gillian. You are right. Recipes centered on delivering good nutrition and flavorful food is key. Of course without the use of all of those ingredients that are so difficult to pronounce. Sometimes it is easy to follow trends to drive profits, but with us wellness is our starting point.

reviews.review_text: Decent selection of lunch items, if you just want a full quick lunch (Hot or Cold) this is great little spot.
I found the fare both delicious, and filling. All at a reasonable price. The world needs more Peqish!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks John. We agree that the world needs more Peqish and more importantly wonderful people like you that share positive words of encouragement and are so kind!

reviews.review_text: I got a chicken double cheese sandwich and pumpkin carrot soup. Delicious!
Damn good sandwiches, healthy, but expensive.

I love the idea of Peqish and I want to love Peqish, but I always leave feeling that I wish something was different. Hand crafted, fresh food to-go. Sounds great right? I thought so, but there is something off about bread sitting in a refrigerated case for multiple hours. The salads are impressive, but just feel expensive. Dont get me wrong... Peqish isnt bad. Its actually decent. Its just not as good as it could be. Staff is always friendly though!

Usually a good place to pick up something fast and healthy (sandwiches, wraps, soup of the day, salads), but it is hit and miss. The sandwiches Ive had seem like the bread is stale. Wraps are good, but could have more in them. Boxed salads are okay. Seared salmon / chicken is my favourite go-to there. Comes with quinoa and a tasty dressing. Actually went in today at ten minutes to 12 to get a lunch. There was already someone waiting at the till when I entered. After looking around, I chose what I wanted and went to the till as well. Nobody was there to serve us!  Several staff were in the back cooking and prepping things, but they didnt acknowledge us or come to the front to man the till. I was in a rush, so I just put the food back and left. Not sure when Ill be returning since there are a lot of other choices around. Peqishs main business is catering, and that fact certainly showed today. When the staff are there at the front, they are nice and friendly.
very delicious food and coffee but not cheap
Always with he broke machine
The wraps and sandwiches are very very dry
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your feedback, Yuri. We have changed the packaging on our sandwiches to address this so they dont dry out.

reviews.review_text: Why? Why do you put so much onion on your sandwiches? I got a tuna sandwich a few weeks ago, or should I say an onion sandwich with hints of tuna. Today I got a Festive Chicken Crancherry sandwich, which once again only tasted of onion. Even on the list of ingredients it mentioned a touch of aioli, but didnt mention the many chunks of raw red onion that appeared in the sandwich. Hope that doesnt mess up people with allergies... Very not impressed. Want a nice sandwich made with local ingredients but want to be able to taste the ingredients I purchased the sandwich for, not the ones not even mentioned on the ingredients list.

Its not sockeye salmon, mislabeling an ingredient in the food biz may be detrimental. Got the salmon sandwich, to discover its a much whiter flesh, and taste was off. Also, theres barely anything inside (equivalent amount of fish that may be on one piece of nigiri sushi for example, thats it for inside the whole sandwich, meat/fish almost non-existent), just mostly the bread, mayo and some lettuce. It looked questionable, but was hopeful there was more to it than met the eye. After a couple bites I realized it was a let down. Not even worth half the price. I showed the staff, only a couple bites in, and explained my dissatisfaction, and no refund was offered.... Update, to address the response from Peqish: I am not interested in ever eating here again, not even for free.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your comment. It is our policy to always ensure that guests are satisfied. Would you please email us directly at info@peqish.com to let us know when you purchased this sandwich and from which location. This will help us investigate. In the meantime, we would be pleased to refund you your money and also buy you lunch. With kind regards, Peqish management.

reviews.review_text: Cold Sandwiches... We ordered from Peqish for our corporate lunch day, I got the ham sandwich. It was cold, dry, stale, and utterly disappointing. I cant speak to the other items here but dont bother with their sandwiches.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Evan. Did you order this through Foodee or directly through Peqish? We take pride in delivering on our quality promise so this information will be important for us to investigate so we can ensure that this doesnt happen to future customers.

reviews.review_text: Peqish takes 30 minutes to prepare a side of fries. They offer extremely limited food options, and none of it is terribly fresh, outside of their baked goods.

This review is for the location in great northern way. Horribly expensive. Takes avg 30 mins to get anything made.they have  1 item menu which they cant even turn in less than 30. Nobody likes this place in our building. We are unfortunately without other options.
did an online order and was told be ready in 2 - 5 minutes and i should go now, upon arrival my order was cancelled .. so much for the time saving...
Bread, cheese and ham, a bit of spinach. The baguette is tiny, more like a 6 inch at subway at twice the price.
Stale/expired sandwich sent me home early from work early.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: I sincerely apologize for your unacceptable experience. May I ask which sandwich you purchased, as well as from which location and when? This will greatly help us determine corrective measures. Many thanks
